Latest Shipping Software Announces eCommerce Marketplace Integrations
PRESS RELEASE FROM
October 24, 2016
Lehi, UT—Shipping software company, ShipCaddie, has announced fresh integrations with several online marketplaces. Online sellers can now seamlessly connect their order management systems from Amazon, eBay and Etsy to the cloud-based shipping software, enabling them to import orders, print shipping labels and ship products to end-users all from the same application. Additionally, ShipCaddie now integrates with any ecommerce website via the popular Shopify ecommerce platform.
In a retail market that continues to trend toward online shopping, shipping software platforms are necessary for management of higher shipment volumes, according to ShipCaddie Founder and CEO Shaun Rothwell.
“We’ve seen an explosion in the ecommerce market that is changing the way orders are processed and shipped to end-users,” says Rothwell. “Rather than large freight orders getting shipped to retail stores, we are seeing deeply fragmented small parcel shipments going directly to residential customers.”
While other popular platforms such as ShipStation, ShipWorks and Shipping Easy have been consolidated under publicly-traded giant Stamps.com, ShipCaddie has emerged as the privately-held alternative for shippers of all sizes. ShipCaddie users have greater flexibility without the user limitations imposed by the publicly-traded subsidiaries that typically bear strict revenue models and complex, nickel-and-dime pricing plans for customers.
ShipCaddie is expected to roll out integration with several additional ecommerce platforms in the coming weeks, including WooCommerce, BigCommerce, Volusion and more. For more information, visithttp://www.shipcaddie.com.
About ShipCaddie: 
ShipCaddie is a cloud-based shipping software that allows businesses to connect their FedEx, UPS, USPS and DHL accounts to their order management systems and ship their products to customers. ShipCaddie enables users to compare carriers and qualify for discounts that are otherwise unavailable, while collecting actionable data that detects opportunities to reduce shipping costs. ShipCaddie is available to parcel shippers and will roll out TL-LTL capabilities in the coming months.

Shipcaddie Profile and History
ShipCaddie is a cloud-based shipping software that allows businesses to connect their FedEx, UPS, USPS and DHL accounts to their order management systems and ship their products to customers. ShipCaddie enables users to compare carriers and qualify for discounts that are otherwise unavailable, while collecting actionable data that detects opportunities to reduce shipping costs.
